Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces. Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Toss with half the @harissa spice mix{2%sachets}, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Arrange the potato pieces cut-side down.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until fork tender, ~{25-35%minutes}.

== Fresh Veg Salsa ==

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces.

Trim the @cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthways) quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Cut the @tomato{2}(cut into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks.

Pop the veg into a #bowl{} and mix to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== Harissa Prawns ==

Roughly chop the @prawns{180%g}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Pop into a bowl along with the remaining harissa spice, salt, pepper and @oil{1%tbsp}. Leave aside to marinate.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left to cook, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the prawns. Fry until cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, pop the @tortilla{8}(to warm) into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season the @creme fraiche{65%g} to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the tomato and onion salsa between the tortillas. Scatter the harissa prawns over the top.

Drizzle over the cooling creme fraiche. Serve with spiced baby potatoes alongside.